        <img src="https://img.freepik.com/free-photo/side-view-rice-garnish-with-fried-onion-carrot-greens-chili-pepper-table_141793-5069.jpg?t=st=1730651321~exp=1730654921~hmac=a54e30539be1e242a7ca9b2f5c011ccd1502a633063ff8313dff83f7b9736c37&w=1380" alt="Biryani" style="width:100%; max-width:600px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px auto;">
        <p><strong>Butter Chicken:</strong> Originating from Delhi, this creamy, mildly spiced curry is made with tandoori-cooked chicken in a rich tomato-butter sauce, often enjoyed with naan or rice.</p>
        <p><strong>Paneer Tikka:</strong> A vegetarian delight, marinated and grilled paneer pieces served with mint chutney.</p>
        <p>Each region of India brings unique flavors to its dishes, from the seafood-rich coastlines of Kerala to the spicy vegetarian fare of Rajasthan. Food is also central to Indian festivals, with sweets and savory treats symbolizing celebration and unity.</p>
